 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Vice President, Business Intelligence Sun Communities, Inc. 316 reviews Southfield, MI 48034 Full-time Sun Communities, Inc. 316 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Position Summary 
The Vice President of Business Intelligence will lead the vision, strategy, and execution for enterprise data to support a data-driven organization. The position is responsible for articulating strategic opportunities for data analytics, machine learning, and AI, for developing and delivering a roadmap of strategic BI goals, for developing resources and supporting analytics needs across business teams, and for driving the data strategy of a complex, growing organization. 
Duties 
Works in close collaboration with business experts, developers, analysts and project teams to understand data requirements, integration needs, constraints, and performance requirements. 
Ensures technical and design documentation is thorough, accessible and continuously maintained. 
Responsible for owning and developing the vision, strategy, and execution for enterprise data & analytics, ensuring scalability of systems, processes, and talent. 
Partners with business leaders to manage an integrated analytics roadmap. 
Lead teams responsible for building and managing technical infrastructure, data platform, and visualization technologies focused on end-users. 
Manage data insights and analytics, including enterprise dashboards and support the creation of functional dashboards in partnership with business functions. 
Oversee and ensure adherance to data governance and data integrity protocols and procedures. 
Lead machine learning and artificial intelligence initiatives. 
Lead high-value technology selection decisions with transparency to business leaders and alignment with enterprise architecture. 
Serve as a visionary and results-oriented leader whose team supports adoption of high-value data insights across the enterprise. 
Provide world-class, self-service data toolset for business users to maximize use of enterprise analytics. 
Ensures data management platforms and structures conform to industry best practices, SOX and other compliance requirements, SOD, audit logging, and data risk management. 
Helps, supports and mentors BI team members, assisting them in project work and helping with planning skill improvements. 
Other duties as assigned. 
Requirements 
Bachelor's Degree in Data Management, Information Technology, Computer Science or related field (Required) 
10+ years related work experience in data architecture, data management, and development 
2 years related work experience in machine learning artificial intelligence (AI) 
5 years experience with broad range of business intelligence (BI) tools 
7 years proven leadership experience building data analytics, data science and data engineering capabilities 
5 years experience selecting and integrating complementary market/consumer data 
Advanced knowledge of database development and data management technologies and processes 
Proven understanding of application development technologies and processes 
Advanced knowledge of data integration processes and technologies 
Hands-on design and development experience with multiple data technologies, including data warehouse, big data, data integration, and ETL 
Knowledge and experience with agile development practices 
Strong attention to detail and multi-tasking skills 
Outstanding business acumen with an understanding of business drivers and how to drive organizational value 
Knowledge and practical application of advanced statistical analysis and mathematical modeling concepts and principles 
Demonstrated track record of building and developing high-performing BI teams 
BENEFITS 
 At Sun Communities, you will be part of an industry-leading organization where you will be challenged, inspired, rewarded and transformed. We place a high priority on our team members, and this is a big part of what sets us apart. We will ask you to give us your very best every day, and will challenge you with interesting work, stretch assignments, a collaborative and supportive work environment and plenty of learning and growth. In exchange, we will reward you with great pay, advancement opportunities, paid time off, great benefits, and flexibility. 
